@page "/design-systems"
<PageTitle>Design Systems - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="design-systems">Design Systems</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="how-it-works">How It Works</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                Saascade components are design-system-agnostic. A single <code>IDesignSystem</code>
                abstraction maps your components to the correct CSS classes for any framework.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <h3>The IDesignSystem Interface</h3>

            <p>
                Every design system implements <code>IDesignSystem</code>, which provides three key methods:
            </p>

            <ul>
                <li><strong>GetComponentName</strong> — returns the CSS class name for a component (e.g. <code>card</code>, <code>btn</code>).</li>
                <li><strong>GetSpecializations</strong> — returns variant classes (e.g. <code>bg-base-100 w-96 shadow-sm</code>).</li>
                <li><strong>GetStyleForComponent</strong> — returns inline styles when needed.</li>
            </ul>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="supported-frameworks">Supported Frameworks</h2>

            <p>
                The <code>CssFramework</code> enum defines the supported targets:
            </p>

            <ul>
                <li><strong>Custom</strong> — no framework, raw HTML/CSS.</li>
                <li><strong>Bootstrap4</strong> — Bootstrap 4 (planned).</li>
                <li><strong>Bootstrap5</strong> — Bootstrap 5 with vanilla classes.</li>
                <li><strong>Tailwind</strong> — Tailwind CSS with DaisyUI or Basecoat plugins.</li>
            </ul>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="available-design-systems">Available Design Systems</h2>

            <ul>
                <li><code>DesignSystems.Bootstrap5.VanillaBootstrap5</code></li>
                <li><code>DesignSystems.Tailwind.DaisyUI</code></li>
                <li><code>DesignSystems.Tailwind.Basecoat</code></li>
                <li><code>DesignSystems.Custom.Basic1</code></li>
                <li><code>DesignSystems.Custom.HanddrawnAssessible</code></li>
                <li><code>DesignSystems.Custom.HanddrawnBlackAndWhite</code></li>
                <li><code>DesignSystems.Custom.HanddrawnColor</code></li>
                <li><code>DesignSystems.Custom.EmptyDesignSystem</code></li>
            </ul>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="bootstrap-setup">Bootstrap 5 Setup</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                Configure Saascade to use Bootstrap 5's vanilla CSS classes across all components.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>builder.Services.AddSingleton&lt;IDesignSystem&gt;(DesignSystems.Bootstrap5.VanillaBootstrap5);</code></pre>

            <p>
                Include <code>&lt;DesignSystemStylesheetReferences /&gt;</code> in your <code>index.html</code>
                to load Bootstrap's CDN stylesheet automatically.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="daisyui-setup">DaisyUI Setup</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                Configure Saascade to use DaisyUI's semantic Tailwind component classes.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>builder.Services.AddSingleton&lt;IDesignSystem&gt;(DesignSystems.Tailwind.DaisyUI);</code></pre>

            <p>
                DaisyUI components support specializations such as <code>bg-base-100</code>,
                <code>w-96</code>, and <code>shadow-sm</code> returned by <code>GetSpecializations()</code>.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="basecoat-setup">Basecoat Setup</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                Configure Saascade to use Basecoat's clean, minimal Tailwind component library.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>builder.Services.AddSingleton&lt;IDesignSystem&gt;(DesignSystems.Tailwind.Basecoat);</code></pre>

            <p>
                Basecoat provides a different aesthetic from DaisyUI while sharing the same
                Tailwind utility foundation. Choose based on your design preferences.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("design-systems", "Design Systems"),
    new TocItem("how-it-works", "How It Works", 2),
    new TocItem("supported-frameworks", "Supported Frameworks", 2),
    new TocItem("available-design-systems", "Available Design Systems", 2),
    new TocItem("bootstrap-setup", "Bootstrap 5 Setup", 2),
    new TocItem("daisyui-setup", "DaisyUI Setup", 2),
    new TocItem("basecoat-setup", "Basecoat Setup", 2)
])" />

</div>
